<subSubSection id="F3403558DF4CAE23D22824EE40A49962" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="5B78F23F7A6FC189FE16DC4AB4FFB256" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A7094AEC09320EDFC54FF5BBBB09FA45" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
North Black Sea coast, Cape Kaliakra, 23.06.2008, 6 w., leg. ALG; East Rhodopes, Strazhets vill., 03.05.2009, 2 w., leg. ALG; Gaberovo vill., 10.04.2013, 7 w., leg. ALG; Oreshari vill., 22.04.2014, 15 w., leg. ALG; Meden buk vill., 22.04.2021, 10 w., leg. ALG; Maleshevska Mt., Gorna Breznitsa vill., 27.03.2012, 1 q., 10 w., leg. ALG; Pirin Mt., Vlahi vill., 27.03.2012, 15 w., leg. ALG; Stara Kresna vill., 06.05.2013, 20 w., leg. ALG; Slavyanka Mt., Goleshovo vill., 04.05.2013, 7 w., leg. ALG. Detailed occurrence data: 
<bibRefCitation id="A25DC2027454264F0883FA6D57A7201E" author="Lapeva-Gjonova, A." journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity Data Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" refId="B7741022" refString="Lapeva-Gjonova, A., Borowiec, L., 2022. New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria. In: Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." title="New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria" volumeTitle="Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." year="2022">Lapeva-Gjonova and Borowiec (2022)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8DFD0B51B37F5B2DA9335D98021B4B4D" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="notes">
<paragraph id="E69B2CD5D2BFFDCE3B76BB2180E49AAB" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DFCD42F6FBC0F66F46DDB542C86F7747" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
<taxonomicName id="9EE060B93D96C9953FEA2228BC513DC8" authorityName="Forel" authorityYear="1889" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Camponotus oertzeni" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oertzeni">
<emphasis id="7CAF2BB441AB79383B4BFE197CFAB10B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Camponotus oertzeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from Greece, Serbia, Iran and Turkey (
<bibRefCitation id="2A560255F07F91D233EA1359BFC6FF6B" author="Borowiec, L." journalOrPublisher="Acta Entomologica Silesiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="1 - 22" refId="B7725669" refString="Borowiec, L., Salata, S., 2018. New records of ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) from Epirus, Greece. Acta Entomologica Silesiana 26: 1 - 22" title="New records of ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) from Epirus, Greece" volume="26" year="2018">Borowiec and Salata 2018</bibRefCitation>
) and its first published record from Bulgaria was given under the name 
<taxonomicName id="0BFFEBA016102E8A034D42D6EFF1BBBB" class="Insecta" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. pilicornis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilicornis">
<emphasis id="CC9365664712A02DF0E0C5A6772C3D3B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">C. pilicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Roger, 1859) in 
<bibRefCitation id="C483316176745D7B16B9AA698660E935" author="Lapeva-Gjonova, A." journalOrPublisher="ZooNotes" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="1 - 6" refId="B7725876" refString="Lapeva-Gjonova, A., Santamaria, S., 2011. First records of Laboulbeniales (Ascomycota) on ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) in Bulgaria. ZooNotes 22: 1 - 6" title="First records of Laboulbeniales (Ascomycota) on ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) in Bulgaria" volume="22" year="2011">Lapeva-Gjonova and Santamaria (2011)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
